Document: EditorUndoRedoManager
Path: godot/classes/class_editorundoredomanager.rst
Summary: EditorUndoRedoManager manages UndoRedo objects for edited scenes, automatically associating actions with the correct scene or a global history, and is primarily for Godot editor plugins.

EditorUndoRedoManager is a manager for UndoRedo objects associated with edited scenes. Each scene has its own undo history and EditorUndoRedoManager ensures that each action performed in the editor gets associated with a proper scene. For actions not related to scenes (ProjectSettings edits, external resources, etc.), a separate global history is used.

The usage is mostly the same as UndoRedo. You create and commit actions and the manager automatically decides under-the-hood what scenes it belongs to. The scene is deduced based on the first operation in an action, using the object from the operation. The rules are as follows:

- If the object is a Node, use the currently edited scene;
- If the object is a built-in resource, use the scene from its path;
- If the object is external resource or anything else, use global history.

This guessing can sometimes yield false results, so you can provide a custom context object when creating an action.

EditorUndoRedoManager is intended to be used by Godot editor plugins. You can obtain it using EditorPlugin.get_undo_redo(). For non-editor uses or plugins that don't need to integrate with the editor's undo history, use UndoRedo instead.

The manager's API is mostly the same as in UndoRedo, so you can refer to its documentation for more examples. The main difference is that EditorUndoRedoManager uses object + method name for actions, instead of Callable.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorUndoRedoManager
Path: godot/classes/class_editorundoredomanager.rst
Summary: This document outlines the methods, signals, and enumerations for managing undo/redo operations within the Godot editor.

Signals:
history_changed(): Emitted when the list of actions in any history has changed, either when an action is committed or a history is cleared.
version_changed(): Emitted when the version of any history has changed as a result of undo or redo call.

Enumerations:
enum SpecialHistory:
GLOBAL_HISTORY = 0: Global history not associated with any scene, but with external resources etc.
REMOTE_HISTORY = -9: History associated with remote inspector. Used when live editing a running project.
INVALID_HISTORY = -99: Invalid "null" history. It's a special value, not associated with any object.

Method: add_do_method(object: Object, method: StringName, ...)
Register a method to be called when the action is committed ("do" action). The `object` determines target history if first operation.

Method: add_do_property(object: Object, property: StringName, value: Variant)
Register a property value change for the "do" action. The `object` determines target history if first operation.

Method: add_do_reference(object: Object)
Register a reference for "do" that will be erased if the "do" history is lost. Useful for new nodes created by the "do" call. Do not use for resources.

Method: add_undo_method(object: Object, method: StringName, ...)
Register a method to be called when the action is undone ("undo" action). The `object` determines target history if first operation.

Method: add_undo_property(object: Object, property: StringName, value: Variant)
Register a property value change for the "undo" action. The `object` determines target history if first operation.

Method: add_undo_reference(object: Object)
Register a reference for "undo" that will be erased if the "undo" history is lost. Useful for nodes removed by the "do" call.

Method: clear_history(id: int = -99, increase_version: bool = true)
Clears the specified undo history. `id` can be for a specific scene, global history, or INVALID_HISTORY for all histories (except REMOTE_HISTORY). If `increase_version` is true, the history version increases, marking it unsaved. Useful for operations that modify the scene, but don't support undo.
GDScript:
    var scene_root = EditorInterface.get_edited_scene_root()
    var undo_redo = EditorInterface.get_editor_undo_redo()
    undo_redo.clear_history(undo_redo.get_object_history_id(scene_root))
Note: To mark an edited scene as unsaved without clearing its history, use EditorInterface.mark_scene_as_unsaved() instead.

Method: commit_action(execute: bool = true)
Commits the current action. If `execute` is true (default), all "do" methods/properties are called/set.

Method: create_action(name: String, merge_mode: MergeMode = 0, custom_context: Object = null, backward_undo_ops: bool = false, mark_unsaved: bool = true)
Creates a new action. Follow with add_do_method(), add_undo_method(), add_do_property(), and add_undo_property() calls, then commit the action with commit_action(). `merge_mode` controls action merging. If `custom_context` is provided, it determines target history. `backward_undo_ops` dictates undo operation order. If `mark_unsaved` is false, the history is not marked unsaved.

Method: force_fixed_history()
Forces the next operation (e.g. add_do_method()) to use the action's history rather than guessing it from the object. Use only when necessary, e.g., for a nested resource without a path. The `custom_context` parameter of create_action() is usually preferred for complex cases.

Method: get_history_undo_redo(id: int) -> UndoRedo
Returns the UndoRedo object associated with the given history `id`. `id` above `0` maps to opened scene tabs; `id` of `0` or lower have special meaning (see SpecialHistory). Best used with get_object_history_id(). Directly operating on the UndoRedo object might affect editor stability.

Method: get_object_history_id(object: Object) -> int
Returns the history ID deduced from the given `object`. It can be used with get_history_undo_redo().

Method: is_committing_action() -> bool
Returns true if the EditorUndoRedoManager is currently committing the action, i.e. running its "do" method or property change (see commit_action()).